<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1903-09-10T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1903-09-10T00:00:00-05:00" n="773" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d773">
                        <head><hi rend="italic">Mr. <persName type="from">Leishman</persName> to Mr.
                                    <persName type="to">Hay</persName>.</hi></head>
                        <opener><seg rendition="#center">[Telegram.—Paraphrase.]</seg></opener>
                        <opener><dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Legation of the United States</hi>,<lb/><hi rend="italic">Constantinople</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1903-09-10"><hi rend="italic">September 10,
                                    1903</hi></date>.</dateline></opener>
                        <p>(Mr. Leishman states that Consul Ravndal reports that Beirut is quiet,
                            but that many of the shops are still closed, as the people have not
                            entirely recovered from their fright of last Sunday.)</p>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>